name: soybean meal to generic market for protein feed | energy feed, gross | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/6586/documentation

This activity is a linking activity, i.e. it connects soybean meal with generic protein feed market. Soybean meal is used mainly as a feed for animals, thus traded on generic feed market with other protein - containing products.

This linking activity has the soybean meal as input and produces protein and energy feed as outputs.
category: C:Manufacturing/10:Manufacture of food products/108:Manufacture of prepared animal feeds/1080:Manufacture of prepared animal feeds

exchanges.description: Calculated based on literature value from Agroscope database (http://www.feed-alp.admin.ch). Agroscope (http://www.agroscope.admin.ch/org/index.html?lang=en) is a research institute which belongs to the Swiss Federal Office for Agriculture. The gross energy in soybean meal might vary depending on the amount of fat present in the meal. This meal is considered to have less than 1.3% of fat. The dry mass of the reference product is 0.89kg/kg.
